  "text": ". Pressure volume loops show abnormalities in morphology, size and orientation. The most common abnormalities are early shortening and early relaxation, with markedly reduced effective work. Early shortening occurs because of the unloading effect of dyskinetic myocardium, which acts as an elastic slack element during isovolumic contraction [CITATION_1] . Within each cardiac cycle, regional P/L loops move in an opposite direction and asynchronously. Each region therefore produces a different contribution to global ejection.",
